Western Cape health officials are concerned about the number of COVID-19 patients in ICU. The province's head of health says what's also worrying is the number of health workers now testing positive for the virus. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Western Cape hospitals are under severe pressure as the number of COVID-19 patients increases. Over 100 of them are in intensive care units in the province. READ: COVID-19: Western Cape health system under pressure The health department said 65 percent of the country's confirmed coronavirus cases are in the province. The head of the Western Cape health department Dr Keith Cloete says more medical staff are contracting the virus, hampering treatment. READ: Nurses suspended over patient's death Cloete also said says ramped-up testing has led to a backlog, but more test kits are being redirected to the Western Cape. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.